The paper discusses optimal solution methods for decentralized partially observable Markov decision processes (Dec-POMDPs), which are models for collaborative multiagent planning under uncertainty. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including artificial intelligence (AI), multi-agent systems (MA), robotics (RO), machine learning (LG), and systems and control (SY). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.LG, and cs.SY, in descending order of likelihood.
